VIII.

About Caninius see i. 3. note.

1. studia. Doring is nearly right when he says that the absolute use of studia in our modern sense of “studies '' is confined to late Latinity. But such phrases as studiis ac litteris (Cic. ad Att. viii. 11), studia exercere (ad Fam. ix. 8), seri studiorum (Hor. Sat. i. 10, 12) show a near approach to the later usage.
